Various allowances for differently abled children in special schools in the government and aided sectors have been revised. The boarding allowance for a student had been fixed at Rs.750 a month, the uniform allowance at Rs.750 a year, request allowance for a student in lower primary school at Rs.50 a year, for upper primary students at Rs.90, and high school students at Rs.200. The boarding allowance has now been hiked to Rs.1,500, which is twice the current allowance of Rs.750 a month, and the uniform allowance to Rs.1,000. â€” Staff Reporter